5. (a) POSITIVE-FEEDBACK LOOPS NOT BOUNDED BY DECAY OR CAP
================================================================================

Bounded loops (OK — have decay, ceiling, per-tick cap, or hysteresis):
  • belief ↔ temple: belief decay ÷500; temple cap 5; institution ±1/tick
  • unrest ↔ garrison: garrison max level 5 → max −10 unrest/tick; per-driver rise caps
  • research → yield/capacity/mitigation: tier-saturated effects (caps at tier 6/9)
  • cohesion ↔ unrest: cohesion decay ÷500; unrest damp divisors capped
  • diplomacy threshold: peace cap +10k, war erosion cap 8k, floor 2k
  • trade volume: arbitrage cap 2×; unrest trade floor 0.5×; cohesion trade cap 1.5×
  • stratification: target clamp [0,1000]; step ≤5/tick
  • food scarcity → births: factor ∈ (0,1], never boosts above natural rate

UNBOUNDED or weakly bounded accumulators (risk flags):

  [U1] TOTAL UNREST — no ceiling on state.unrest
       Drivers can stack every tick (food + energy + overcrowding + inequality +
       dispossession + agent_misery) while only the *rise* is damped (min ÷1 after
       cohesion/research damp). Decay path requires food abundance (−10/tick only).
       Sustained multi-driver hardship → unrest grows without asymptotic cap.

  [U2] TOTAL COHESION — no ceiling on state.cohesion
       Only floor 0 and proportional decay ÷500. If belief inflow persistently exceeds
       unrest fray, cohesion accumulates without upper bound (effects saturate via
       divisors but scalar does not).

  [U3] RESEARCH_PROGRESS — no ceiling on accumulator
       Tier-derived effects saturate, but research_progress itself is unbounded
       (linear +population +cohesion bonus forever).

  [U4] UNREST → BELIEF HARDSHIP (+unrest/100) — uncapped inflow
       Unlike other unrest drivers, faith_from_hardship has no per-tick cap.
       High unrest injects belief linearly; belief has ÷500 decay but no hard max.
       Creates belief→cohesion→unrest-damp negative arm, yet belief injection scales
       with unrest without bound → slow drift to high-belief/high-unrest equilibrium.

  [U5] CLUSTER_STOCKS (phase_life) — unbounded food accumulation
       Each cluster member adds +1 food/tick to cluster_stocks with NO decay, cap,
       or consumer. Stocks never feed faction_resources, market supply, or agent needs.
       Pure integrator — strongest unbounded dead accumulator in the tick loop.

  [U6] INSTITUTION UPKEEP → TREASURY DRAIN → INEQUALITY → UNREST (weak bound)
       Poorest-faction treasury floored at 0, but spread can widen without bound as
       rich factions accumulate via trade/diplomacy. No explicit coupling from upkeep
       back into stratification except via spread→inequality (per-tick cap 25).

