================================================================================

Confirmed dead or display-only outputs (written but not read by any later phase
or policy function in the tick DAG):

  [D1] phase_chronicle → chronicle, chronicle_tech_seen, chronicle_age
       Only exposed via chronicle() getter for UI/serialization. No feedback into
       economy, diplomacy, agents, or institutions.

  [D2] phase_life → cluster_stocks
       Accumulates per-settlement food; only cluster_stocks() getter (HUD). Does not
       affect resources, market_state, faction_resources, or agent LifeNeeds.

  [D3] phase_emergence → EmergenceState cluster_cultures, SocialGraph, agent Psyche.beliefs
       Culture drift and agent beliefs update ECS only. Macro state.belief is a
       separate scalar (phase_belief); agent beliefs never aggregate upward.
       SocialGraph ties do not affect diplomacy, trade, or faction_relations.

  [D4] phase_emergence → legends graph, emergence_feed, civ_ai_decisions
       Ingest/narration path only (legends charter: "never a generator of outcomes").
       Saga promotions and civ-ai names do not alter WorldState or phase inputs.

  [D5] phase_tech → TECH_STORAGE, TECH_METALLURGY bits
       Bits are OR'd into tech_unlocks but no phase reads these flags (unlike
       IRRIGATION/SANITATION/WRITING/GUNPOWDER). Traceability doc lists this as
       an open gap.

  [D6] phase_economic_focus → EconomicFocus::Sacred | Mercantile
       candidate_economic_focus can select these, but phase_production only bonuses
       Agrarian and Industrial. Sacred/Mercantile are labels without mechanical effect.

  [D7] phase_life → last_settlement_count
