7. (c) TOP 5 HIGHEST-LEVERAGE MISSING COUPLINGS (emergence charter)
================================================================================

Charter requires society/economy/belief/politics to EMERGE with bidirectional
coupling; hardcode only physical/genomic law. Ranked by leverage × charter gap:

  [M1] AGENT CULTURE/PSYCHE → MACRO SOCIETY (belief, unrest, cohesion, diplomacy)
       Gap: phase_emergence builds cluster_cultures, Psyche.beliefs, SocialGraph;
       macro state.belief/unrest/cohesion ignore them. Charter: "Ideology & culture
       drift across populations" should shape collective behavior.
       Fix vector: aggregate homophily/ideology dispersion into cohesion_delta,
       diplomacy threshold, or market trust — close micro↔macro loop.

  [M2] SETTLEMENT CLUSTER_STOCKS → ECONOMY (supply, prices, faction_resources)
       Gap: phase_life commons accumulate food with no sink; phase_economy market
       supply uses carrying_capacity only, not settlement production.
       Charter: "Markets emerge from local resource/scarcity conditions"; settlements
       are emergent economic units (phase_life comment: "collective economics").
       Fix vector: cluster_stocks → faction_resources or market apply_pressure supply.

  [M3] TECH_STORAGE / TECH_METALLURGY → PRODUCTION & TRADE
       Gap: bits set at tier 2/3 but never read (dead tech silo).
       Charter: technology emerges from research, not enum slots; unlocked capabilities
       should change material outcomes.
       Fix vector: STORAGE dampens food price volatility or spoilage; METALLURGY boosts
       metal yield / industrial building_demand (traceability open gap row).

  [M4] EMERGENT CLUSTER/POLITY IDENTITY → DIPLOMACY & FACTION DYNAMICS
       Gap: diplomacy uses hardcoded faction:u32 keys + treasury disparity coin-flip
       structure; ClusterMember from phase_life does not define polity membership.
       Charter: "Polities emerge from co-location + kinship + culture"; "faction is
       one possible shape"; membership is cluster overlap NOT faction:u32.
       Fix vector: derive diplomatic pairs from cluster contact edges / culture distance;
       let faction_relations emerge from settlement interaction not static ids.

  [M5] INSTITUTION UPKEEP & DISPOSSESSED SHARE → PRODUCTION / LABOR OUTPUT
       Gap: institution drain hits poorest treasury only; dispossessed_permille feeds
       unrest but not production_yield or faction_resources.
       Charter: social stratification should emerge from economic payoff + coercion,
       feeding back into economy not just unrest scalar.
       Fix vector: dispossessed_permille scales production_yield_factor or farm output;
       temple/garrison upkeep widens treasury spread intentionally (traceability
       candidate: "institution upkeep → faction inequality feedback").

